id: jf-fdh1
title: Correct stale post-release documentation and runtime prerequisites
description: "The release process and readiness guide still describe jellyfin-cli as unreleased and tell maintainers to keep the changelog in a first-release reset state despite published v2026.3.4 and v2026.3.6 releases. The dependency modernization also raises the supported runtime floor, which must be explicit in setup and contributor docs."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: documentation,maintenance,node,release
created_at: "2026-07-16T16:55:50.930Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-16T17:00:22.428Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-16T17:00:22.427Z"
author: codex
acceptance_criteria: No active release documentation claims the project is pre-first-release.; Node and Bun prerequisites match CI and package metadata.; Session JSON and Toon playback fields are documented.
goal: jf-mqpo
parent: jf-kpor
severity: medium
environment: "README.md, CONTRIBUTING.md, docs/release-process.md, docs/release-readiness.md, docs/api.md, and docs/toon-format.md"
resolution: "Documented Node 22.13 and Bun 1.3.11, corrected published-release lifecycle guidance, documented session playback formats, and updated the changelog."
expected_result: "Maintainer and user docs reflect current runtime, output, and release state."
actual_result: All identified stale release/runtime statements were corrected and the child Toon contract issue is closed.
customer_impact: Maintainers can follow obsolete release instructions and users may install on unsupported Node versions or miss machine-readable playback behavior.
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-16T17:00:05.556Z",codex,"Updated Node/Bun prerequisites,session output docs,release lifecycle language,release readiness guidance,and Unreleased changelog."
close_reason: Release and runtime documentation is current.
